üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 9: Hacker Classes, Red/Blue/Grey Teams, Attacker Goals, Skills of Ethical Hacker
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. A hacker who breaks into systems for malicious intent is called:
A. White Hat
B. Grey Hat
C. Black Hat
D. Ethical Hacker

2. Ethical hackers work with:
A. Hidden identity
B. Permission
C. Malware
D. Exploits only

3. Which team is responsible for defending systems?
A. Red Team
B. Blue Team
C. Grey Team
D. Black Team

4. Red Team primarily focuses on:
A. Defense
B. Monitoring
C. Attacking to test security
D. Policy writing

5. Grey Hat hackers act:
A. Fully legally
B. Fully illegally
C. Between ethical and unethical
D. Only for money

6. Crackers are mainly involved in:
A. Improving security
B. Breaking software protection
C. Writing policies
D. Network monitoring

7. Goals of attackers usually include:
A. Improving performance
B. Stealing data
C. Increasing availability
D. Strengthening systems

8. The Security‚ÄìFunctionality‚ÄìEase of Use triangle shows that:
A. All three can be maximized
B. Improving one impacts others
C. Security is independent
D. Usability has no effect

9. Ethical hackers aim to:
A. Cause damage
B. Identify and report vulnerabilities
C. Exploit users
D. Bypass law

10. Skills of an ethical hacker include:
A. Only programming
B. Only networking
C. Technical + analytical skills
D. Hardware repair

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which hacker class is hired by organizations?
A. Black Hat
B. Grey Hat
C. White Hat
D. Script Kiddie

12. Script kiddies differ from ethical hackers because they:
A. Write advanced exploits
B. Use ready-made tools
C. Follow laws
D. Report vulnerabilities

13. Blue Team activities include:
A. Penetration testing
B. Vulnerability exploitation
C. Incident detection and response
D. Social engineering

14. Red Team vs Blue Team exercises mainly test:
A. Hardware efficiency
B. Real-world security readiness
C. UI quality
D. Database speed

15. Which is NOT a typical attacker goal?
A. Data theft
B. Privilege escalation
C. Service disruption
D. Improving user trust

16. Grey Team combines roles of:
A. Red and Black
B. Blue and Black
C. Red and Blue
D. White and Black

17. Ease of use often conflicts with security because:
A. Users prefer complexity
B. Users make mistakes
C. Strong security reduces usability
D. Security is optional

18. Ethical hackers must have knowledge of:
A. Networking and OS
B. Security tools
C. Laws and ethics
D. All of the above

19. Which role focuses on continuous monitoring?
A. Red Team
B. Blue Team
C. Grey Team
D. Hacktivist

20. Attacker goals help ethical hackers to:
A. Write malware
B. Predict attack paths
C. Avoid documentation
D. Disable antivirus

